## Superseded from mojo-jit-emits-avx512-on-non-avx512-cpu

```yaml
name: mojo-jit-emits-avx512-on-non-avx512-cpu
description: "Root cause of modular/modular#6413: Mojo 1.0.0b2.dev2026050805 emits AVX-512 instructions on Azure GHA runners whose CPU does NOT advertise AVX-512..."
category: debugging
date: 2026-05-12
version: "3.0.0"
user-invocable: false
verification: verified-ci
tags: [mojo, jit, avx-512, avx512, sigill, libKGEN, modular-6413, cpu-detection,
       azure-runner, gha, runtime-codegen, zen4, epyc, hyper-v, llvm-host-cpu-detection]
```

AMD EPYC Zen 4 under Microsoft Hyper-V: hypervisor masks AVX-512 CPUID leaves but not
family/model. LLVM getHostCPUName() returns znver4; X86TargetParser.cpp::Processors[] applies
static AVX-512 feature list without cross-checking masked leaves. 20/20 bare-command crashes
confirmed. Smoking gun: mojo build --print-effective-target reports znver4 + 12 +avx512* features
while cpuid(7,0).ebx AVX512F=0. GHA runs 25778579617 (mechanism) and 25778580407 (repro).

